<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870303-0098 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News:Stone Container Declares2-for-1 Split, Lifts Payout</HL><DD> 03/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> STODIVIDENDS (DIV)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><DATELINE> CHICAGO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Stone Container Corp. declared a 2-for-1 stock split and increased its quarterly dividend 33 1/3% on pre-split shares.    The maker of paperboard and paper packaging products raised the dividend to 20 cents a share from 15 cents a share. The increased payout and stock split are both payable June 12 to stock of record May 22.    The company, which has about 16.5 million shares outstanding, cited its confidence in the continuation of the company's increasing earnings performance. It had 1986 net income of $35.4 million, or $1.95 a share, on sales of $2.03 billion. In 1985, net was $3.8 million, or 24 cents a share, on sales of $1.2 billion. </TEXT></DOC>